\section{Capital Market and Renewable Energy Projects}
\subsection{Renewable Energy Finance}

\frame{\frametitle{Renewable Energy Projects}
\begin{itemize}
\item<1-> To meet their 2020 target the EU needs institutional investor (pension funds, insurance companies, wealth managers) money as banks and utilities are facing severe constraints on their long-term capital available.
\item<2-> Regulatory barriers
\begin{itemize}
\item pension funds are not allowed to invest in infrastructure 
\item unbundling: funds are not allowed to invest in generation, if they are invested in transmission and distribution
\item Solvency II requires additional regulatory capital for illiquid assets
\end{itemize}
\item<3->
Governmental support schemes seem to be unstable, which increases the investment risk for investing in renewable energy projects. 
\end{itemize}
}

