\frame{\frametitle{Climate Bonds Basics}
\begin{itemize}
\item<1-> Climate bonds are fixed-income financial instruments (bonds) linked in some way to climate change solutions., which are issued in order to raise finance for climate change projects. 
\item<2-> Project can be greenhouse gas emission reduction projects ranging from clean energy  to energy efficiency, or climate change adaptation projects ranging from building Nile  delta flood defences to helping the Great Barrier Reef adapt to warming waters.
\item<3->
 Climate Bonds can be issued by governments, multi-national banks or corporations. The issuing entity guarantees to repay the bond over a certain period of time, plus either a fixed or variable rate of return.
 \item<4-> see \url{ http://www.climatebonds.net}
\end{itemize}
}


